    pearls: ["Filaggrin mutations are found in 30-50% of moderate-severe AD patients - FLG genotyping is emerging as a tool for disease severity prediction and personalized therapy", "The 'atopic march' describes the natural progression from AD in infancy to allergic rhinitis and asthma in childhood - early aggressive AD treatment may modify this progression", "Staphylococcus aureus colonizes >90% of AD skin through binding to fibronectin exposed by barrier dysfunction - its superantigens activate T cells polyclonally, exacerbating inflammation", "Bleach baths (0.005% sodium hypochlorite, approximately 1/4-1/2 cup per full bath, 2-3 times per week for 5-10 minutes) reduce S. aureus colonization and decrease flare frequency", "Dupilumab-associated conjunctivitis is a class-specific effect not seen with other biologics - mechanism may involve IL-13 blockade affecting conjunctival goblet cell mucin production"],
